<bibRefCitation id="EFAE4B36FF83FFC6FC21FAF0DC8AFA96" author="Spencer" box="[1009,1167,1331,1356]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" refString="Spencer, K. A. (1963) A synopsis of the Neotropical Agromyzidae (Diptera). Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London, 115, 291 - 389. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1963. tb 00811. x" type="journal article" year="1963">
Spencer 
<number id="3DF724E0FF83FFC6FB83FAF7DC8AFA96" box="[1107,1167,1331,1356]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" value="1963.0">1963</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C325654CFF83FFC6FF17FA93DD29FA62" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8036C7FF83FFC6FF17FA93DD29FA62" blockId="2.[151,1436,1259,1968]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159">
<emphasis id="B94BEAD5FF83FFC6FF17FA93D94DFAAA" bold="true" box="[199,328,1367,1392]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159">Comments</emphasis>
. Four of five specimens identified by Becker as 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D44FF83FFC6FC16FA9CDCB8FAAA" authority="Fall." authorityName="Fall." box="[966,1213,1367,1392]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Agromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aeneiventris">
<emphasis id="B94BEAD5FF83FFC6FC16FA9CDC7CFAB5" box="[966,1145,1368,1391]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="159">A. aeneiventris</emphasis>
Fall.
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D44FF83FFC6FB37FA93D971FA4E" authority="Fall." authorityName="Fall." class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aeneoventris">
<emphasis id="B94BEAD5FF83FFC6FB37FA93D923FA4E" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="159">Melanagromyza aeneoventris</emphasis>
(Fall.)
</taxonomicName>
, a Palaearctic species) were examined. These represent three different species: 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D44FF83FFC6FB37FABFD8B9FA62" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lini">
<emphasis id="B94BEAD5FF83FFC6FB37FABFD8B9FA62" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="159">Melanagromyza lini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D44FF83FFC6FF1BFA64DA1CFA62" authority="Spencer 1973" authorityName="Spencer" authorityYear="1973" box="[203,537,1439,1464]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="memoranda">
<emphasis id="B94BEAD5FF83FFC6FF1BFA64D973FA62" box="[203,374,1439,1464]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="159">M. memoranda</emphasis>
Spencer 
<number id="3DF724E0FF83FFC6FE0EFA64DA1CFA62" box="[478,537,1440,1464]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" value="1973.0">1973</number>
</taxonomicName>
; and a new species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D44FF83FFC6FD2CFA5BDC60FA62" authority="Boucher" authorityName="Boucher" box="[764,1125,1439,1464]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pontis">
<emphasis id="B94BEAD5FF83FFC6FD2CFA5BDBF9FA6D" box="[764,1020,1439,1464]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="159">Melanagromyza pontis</emphasis>
Boucher
</taxonomicName>
, described below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C325654CFF83FFC6FF17FA07D93BF86A" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8B8036C7FF83FFC6FF17FA07D93BF86A" blockId="2.[151,1436,1259,1968]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159">
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D44FF83FFC6FF17FA07D9AFFA06" box="[199,426,1475,1500]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lini">
<emphasis id="B94BEAD5FF83FFC6FF17FA07D9AFFA06" box="[199,426,1475,1500]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="159">Melanagromyza lini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first described from 
<collectingCountry id="F3287657FF83FFC6FD03FA00DB03FA01" box="[723,774,1476,1499]" name="Peru" pageId="2" pageNumber="159">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFAE4B36FF83FFC6FCC7FA00DBB0FA06" author="Spencer" box="[791,949,1475,1500]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" refString="Spencer, K. A. (1963) A synopsis of the Neotropical Agromyzidae (Diptera). Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London, 115, 291 - 389. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1963. tb 00811. x" type="journal article" year="1963">
Spencer 
<number id="3DF724E0FF83FFC6FCACFA07DBB0FA06" box="[892,949,1475,1500]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" value="1963.0">1963</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and was later recorded in 
<collectingCountry id="F3287657FF83FFC6FB22FA07DD2BFA06" box="[1266,1326,1475,1500]" name="Chile" pageId="2" pageNumber="159">Chile</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFAE4B36FF83FFC6FA90FA00D9EEF9DA" author="Spencer" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" refString="Spencer, K. A. (1982) Agromyzidae (Diptera) in Chile. Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde. Serie A (Biologie), 357, 1 - 55." type="journal article" year="1982">
Spencer 
<number id="3DF724E0FF83FFC6FF47FA2CD8D7F9DA" box="[151,210,1512,1536]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" value="1982.0">1982</number>
, as 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D44FF83FFC6FF2AFA2CD9EEF9DA" authority="Spencer" authorityName="Spencer" box="[250,491,1511,1536]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aguilerai">
<emphasis id="B94BEAD5FF83FFC6FF2AFA2CD980F9DA" box="[250,389,1511,1536]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="159">M. aguilerai</emphasis>
Spencer
</taxonomicName>
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry id="F3287657FF83FFC6FE2EFA23DA68F9DA" box="[510,621,1511,1536]" name="Argentina" pageId="2" pageNumber="159">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFAE4B36FF83FFC6FDABFA23DB3DF9DA" author="Sasakawa" box="[635,824,1511,1536]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" refString="Sasakawa, M. (1992 a) The Neotropical Agromyzidae (Diptera). Part 1. New or little-known species from Argentina. Japanese Journal of Entomology, 60, 346 - 357." type="journal article" year="1992" yearSuffix="a">
Sasakawa 
<number id="3DF724E0FF83FFC6FD22FA2CDB2EF9DA" box="[754,811,1512,1536]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" value="1992.0">1992</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry id="F3287657FF83FFC6FCA6FA23DBE1F9DA" box="[886,996,1511,1536]" name="Colombia" pageId="2" pageNumber="159">Colombia</collectingCountry>
(Sanabria de 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAE4B36FF83FFC6FBAEFA23DD1FF9DA" author="Arevalo" box="[1150,1306,1511,1536]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" refString="Sanabria de Arevalo, I. (1994) Insectos minadores (Diptera: Agromyzidae) de la Sabana de Bogota (Cundinamarca, Colombia). Revista Colombiana de Entomologia, 20, 61 - 100." type="journal article" year="1994">
Arévalo 
<number id="3DF724E0FF83FFC6FB0EFA2CDD1FF9DA" box="[1246,1306,1512,1536]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" value="1994.0">1994</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Important characters observed are: width of frons 
<number id="3DF724E0FF83FFC6FDB5F9C8DA8DF9FE" box="[613,648,1548,1572]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" value="1.4">1.4</number>
times eye width in dorsal view; upper eye distinctly pilose in male (apparently bare in 
<typeStatus id="54848865FF83FFC6FEA3F9EBD9D0F992" box="[371,469,1583,1608]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159">holotype</typeStatus>
but eyes shriveled); 
<number id="3DF724E0FF83FFC6FD12F9F4DAD5F992" box="[706,720,1584,1608]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" value="2.0">2</number>
reclinate ors and 
<number id="3DF724E0FF83FFC6FC4AF9F4DBADF992" box="[922,936,1584,1608]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" value="3.0">3</number>
inclinate ori; orbital setulae in two irregular rows; orbit subshining, not widening anteriorly; parafacial absent or slightly projecting, forming only narrow ring (cheek) below eye; gena deepest at midpoint, about 
<number id="3DF724E0FF83FFC6FD38F9B3DB1CF94A" box="[744,793,1655,1680]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" value="0.25">0.25</number>
times maximum height of eye; antennal bases separated by narrow, slightly elevated keel; third antennal segment small, rounded with very short whitish pubescence at apex; only one notopleural seta visible in Ecuadorian male, two in 
<typeStatus id="54848865FF83FFC6FC54F97BDBE3F902" box="[900,998,1727,1752]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159">holotype</typeStatus>
and in female; mesonotum with bluish and greenish reflection; abdomen distinctly coppery; calypter and fringe white; wing length 
<quantity id="4CC79B22FF83FFC6FB63F927DD0FF921" box="[1203,1290,1763,1788]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" unit="mm" value="2.6">2.6 mm</quantity>
in male (
<quantity id="4CC79B22FF83FFC6FAA8F927D8C6F8C5" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.6 mm</quantity>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAE4B36FF83FFC6FF37F8C3D9B1F8FA" author="Sasakawa" box="[231,436,1799,1824]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" refString="Sasakawa, M. (1992 a) The Neotropical Agromyzidae (Diptera). Part 1. New or little-known species from Argentina. Japanese Journal of Entomology, 60, 346 - 357." type="journal article" year="1992" yearSuffix="a">
Sasakawa (
<number id="3DF724E0FF83FFC6FEB5F8CCD99AF8FA" box="[357,415,1800,1824]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" value="1992.0">1992</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
was probably an error) and 
<quantity id="4CC79B22FF83FFC6FD22F8CCDB4CF8C5" box="[754,841,1800,1824]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" unit="mm" value="2.9">2.9 mm</quantity>
in female. Male genitalia with broad hypandrial arm and short apodeme (
<figureCitation id="13042A42FF83FFC6FEA9F8EFD9E1F89E" box="[377,484,1835,1860]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1136,1159]" captionTargetBox="[347,1240,198,1110]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[340,1247,193,1115]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Melanagromyza lini Spencer, (1) phallus, lateral, (2) phallus, ventral, (3) hypandrium and epandrium. Inset shows hypandrium of freshly dissected specimen, (4) hypandrium and phallus, holotype, permanent mount, (5) ejaculatory apodeme. Inset shows freshly dissected specimen, (6) epandrium, lateroventral. Scale bars = 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252253/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="159">Figs. 3, 4</figureCitation>
). Ejaculatory apodeme with narrow blade, slightly more expanded on knob side (
<figureCitation id="13042A42FF83FFC6FABFF8EFD8A2F8B2" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1136,1159]" captionTargetBox="[347,1240,198,1110]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[340,1247,193,1115]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Melanagromyza lini Spencer, (1) phallus, lateral, (2) phallus, ventral, (3) hypandrium and epandrium. Inset shows hypandrium of freshly dissected specimen, (4) hypandrium and phallus, holotype, permanent mount, (5) ejaculatory apodeme. Inset shows freshly dissected specimen, (6) epandrium, lateroventral. Scale bars = 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252253/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="159">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF724E0FF83FFC6FF47F88BD8A2F8B2" box="[151,167,1871,1896]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
, right side), with strong medial vein. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAE4B36FF83FFC6FD57F88BDB59F8B2" author="Sasakawa" box="[647,860,1871,1896]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" refString="Sasakawa, M. (1992 c) The Neotropical Agromyzidae (Diptera). Part 4. New or little-known species from Peru, Venezuela, Brazil and Bolivia. Scientific Reports of the Kyoto Prefectural University Agriculture, 44, 1 - 33." type="journal article" year="1992" yearSuffix="c">
Sasakawa (
<number id="3DF724E0FF83FFC6FCDEF894DB4CF8B2" box="[782,841,1872,1896]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" value="1992.0">1992</number>
c)
</bibRefCitation>
correctly pointed out that the surstylus is not conspicuously narrowing as described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAE4B36FF83FFC6FDB9F8B0DB11F856" author="Spencer" box="[617,788,1907,1932]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" refString="Spencer, K. A. (1963) A synopsis of the Neotropical Agromyzidae (Diptera). Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London, 115, 291 - 389. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1963. tb 00811. x" type="journal article" year="1963">
Spencer (
<number id="3DF724E0FF83FFC6FD02F8B7DB09F856" box="[722,780,1907,1932]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" value="1963.0">1963</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and does not bear a few “short hairs” but rather numerous spines (
<figureCitation id="13042A42FF83FFC6FF3CF853D935F86A" box="[236,304,1943,1968]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1136,1159]" captionTargetBox="[347,1240,198,1110]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[340,1247,193,1115]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Melanagromyza lini Spencer, (1) phallus, lateral, (2) phallus, ventral, (3) hypandrium and epandrium. Inset shows hypandrium of freshly dissected specimen, (4) hypandrium and phallus, holotype, permanent mount, (5) ejaculatory apodeme. Inset shows freshly dissected specimen, (6) epandrium, lateroventral. Scale bars = 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252253/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="159">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF724E0FF83FFC6FEF0F853D935F86A" box="[288,304,1943,1968]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
